E.D.I.T.H. ("Even Dead, I'm The Hero")
======================================

E.D.I.T.H. is a hybrid fork. It builds on two upstream open-source projects,
both used under the MIT License. Their original LICENSE terms and copyright
notices are retained.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Core ("brain") — forked from Hermes Agent
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Project:   Hermes Agent
Author:    Nous Research
License:   MIT (Copyright (c) 2025 Nous Research)  — see LICENSE
Source:    https://github.com/NousResearch/hermes-agent
Forked at: commit 0428945b5b07f430e23b4fc28b2bff6887477463 (2026-06-14)

The Hermes git history is preserved in this repository and tracked as the
git remote "upstream" so improvements can be pulled in over time. E.D.I.T.H.
modifies and extends this codebase.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Channel capabilities — ported from OpenClaw
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Project:   OpenClaw
Author:    OpenClaw Foundation
License:   MIT (Copyright (c) 2026 OpenClaw Foundation)
Source:    https://github.com/openclaw/openclaw

Selected channel-adapter concepts and capabilities are ported from OpenClaw's
TypeScript extensions into E.D.I.T.H.'s Python gateway. Attribution is retained
in the ported modules.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
Build orchestration — ruflo
------------------------------------------------------------------------------
ruflo (v3.10.x) is used as a BUILD-TIME orchestration tool only (swarm,
autopilot, memory, MCP). It is NOT a runtime dependency of E.D.I.T.H.

------------------------------------------------------------------------------
The prior v0.1 fresh-build prototype is archived under legacy/v0.1/ and is being
ported onto this fork (stealth browser, skill protection lock, memory
namespacing, authorization gate).
